summary: I’m seriously so desperate for a Critical Role animated series. The Vox Machina characters are just so unique, genuine, and...
body: I’m seriously so desperate for a Critical Role animated series. The Vox Machina characters are just so unique, genuine, and funny that they’re worthy of being animated. Even if they kept everything the same down to the tee when it comes to the major story arcs, battles, and highlights, you best believe ima be in front of my screen crying, laughing and cheering over shit I already knew was going to happen. And while, even if it does happen, it won’t be for many, MANY years, I really think it would be a good way to tie the series together, full circle and all.

“If I fall, you will rise. That is my hope.”

Yeah, well, I just fell on the floor to curl up in a ball and cry.

Hey quick question, Liam O’Brien, how do you put so much emotion into a voice that, as I already mentioned, sounds like a busted Speak and Spell.
